land, United Kingdom","Kingston, Dorset, England":"Kingston, Dorset, England","Radipole, Weymouth and Portland Borough, Dorset, England":"Radipole, Dorset, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1385–1451":"circa 1385–1451","1385–1451":"1385–1451","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1401–1463":"1401–1463","1415–Female":"1415–Overleden","1362–1410":"1362–1410","–Female":"Overleden","1451":"1451","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","Abt 1415":"circa 1415","1415":"1415","1401":"1401","1335":"1335","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1463":"1463","about 1401":"circa 1401","about 1385":"circa 1385","1438":"1438","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of,, ENGLAND":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Weymouth, Dorset, England":"Weymouth, Dorset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Kingston, Dorset, England":"Kingston, Dorset, England","Radipole, Weymouth and Portland Borough, Dorset, England":"Radipole, Dorset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1385–1451":"about 1385–1451","1385–1451":"1385–1451","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1401–1463":"1401–1463","1415–Female":"1415–Deceased","1362–1410":"1362–1410","–Female":"Deceased","1451":"1451","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","Abt 1415":"about 1415","1415":"1415","1401":"1401","1335":"1335","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1463":"1463","about 1401":"about 1401","about 1385":"about 1385","1438":"1438","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of,, ENGLAND":"England, United Kingdom","Weymouth, Dorset, England":"Weymouth, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","Kingston, Dorset, England":"Kingston, Dorset, England","Radipole, Weymouth and Portland Borough, Dorset, England":"Radipole, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"la","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Cuong, Anh, Thanh, Ha, Hoang, Tuan, Chau, Hao, Hien, Hoa, Hue, Nam, Phong, Sinh, Tuong, Min, Tam, Tanh, Thai, Tham, Tinh, Yeong.  Chinese Hong, Hang, Sang, Tong, Chan, Chi, Hwa Ja, Hyung, Kam, Ki Bong, Kin, Man.","Vietnamese: from the Chinese surname 羅, see   Luo   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Lã</b>): from the Chinese surname 呂, see   Lu   6 and 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Luo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Yi, Ping, Yong, Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Tour","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  African/Muslim Mamadou, Oumar, Abdoulaye, Amadou, Ibrahima, Mohamed, Sekou, Askia, Bakary, Daouda, Moctar, Moussa, Omar, Seydou, Abdullah, Aboubacar, Ahmed, Aisha, Aliou, Aminata, Babacar, Boubacar, Cherif, Elhadji.","West African (mainly Mali, Guinea, Ivory Coast, and Senegal; <b>Touré</b>): from the name of the Touré clan of the Soninke and the closely related Mandinka peoples, which is from a Soninke word meaning ‘elephant’. This surname is also found among some other peoples, e.g. the Tukulors. Compare   Touray   and   Turay  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Touray","meanings":["West African (mainly Gambia): variant of <b>Touré</b> (see   Toure  ). Compare   Turay  ."]},{"name":"Turay","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  African/Muslim Mohamed, Zainab, Alieu, Ismail, Ahmed, Alimamy, Fatmata, Foday, Hamid, Ibrahim, Idrissa, Isata, Isatu, Kadiatu, Khadijah, Mamadou, Mohammed, Ramatu.","West African (mainly Sierra Leone and Liberia): from a variant of the name of the <b>Touré</b> (see   Toure  ) clan of the Mandinka and, subsequently, Sierra Leonean Limba and Temne peoples. Compare   Touray  .","Hungarian: habitational name for someone from a place called Tura."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de la Tour was born about 1385, in Kingston, Dorset, England as the daughter of Jean de la Tour and Blynchesfield. She married Stephen Russell in 1400, in Weymouth, Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1451, at the age of 67, and was buried in Radipole, Dorset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1385–1451":"umbes 1385–1451","1385–1451":"1385–1451","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1401–1463":"1401–1463","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","1362–1410":"1362–1410","–Female":"Surnud","1451":"1451","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","Abt 1415":"umbes 1415","1415":"1415","1401":"1401","1335":"1335","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1463":"1463","about 1401":"umbes 1401","about 1385":"umbes 1385","1438":"1438","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of,, ENGLAND":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Weymouth, Dorset, England":"Weymouth, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kingston, Dorset, England":"Kingston, Dorset, England","Radipole, Weymouth and Portland Borough, Dorset, England":"Radipole, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1385–1451":"noin 1385–1451","1385–1451":"1385–1451","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1401–1463":"1401–1463","1415–Female":"1415–Kuollut","1362–1410":"1362–1410","–Female":"Kuollut","1451":"1451","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","Abt 1415":"noin 1415","1415":"1415","1401":"1401","1335":"1335","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1463":"1463","about 1401":"noin 1401","about 1385":"noin 1385","1438":"1438","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of,, ENGLAND":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Weymouth, Dorset, England":"Weymouth, Dorset, Engl